            <scopecontent id="aspace_7ef7fabff1b9e84470ba95561ee2a26a">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>This is a collection of materials concerning Luther Newton Hayes (1883-1979?), who was born in China and collected many Chinese documents and artifacts. The leading feature of the collection is a set of lantern slides of the Great Wall. According to Hayes' wife, these were taken by Hayes and William E. Geil. (After Geil's death, Hayes hired two landscape artists in Shanghai to color them.) Hayes used the slides in a lecture presentation; a printed version of the lecture is in the collection. The papers were given by Mrs. L. Newton Hayes in September, 1979, and July, 1980 to the Yale-China Association and subsequently transferred to Manuscripts and Archives.</p>
            </scopecontent>
